Dave Heeley finished the Marathon des Sables on Friday after running 156 miles in six days . 
  The father-of-three from West Bromwich is the first blind man to finish the 'toughest foot race on Earth' in the Sahara Desert . 
  Competitors carry provisions on their backs and have to sleep in tents . 
  Mr Heely was the first man to run seven marathons on seven continents in 2008 . 
 